               <head>Tuhfat al-vuzara’</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tuḥfat al-vuzarā’</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068451" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15973-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20878">Tuḥfat al-vuzarā’</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20878"> تحفة الوزراء </title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A brief work on ethics comprising forty chapters (bāb), each of which consists of a maxim mentioning four things or matters. The author is not identified. In the present manuscript, the text concludes, and was clearly intended to conclude, with Bāb 37, the content of which (at least in this manuscript; see below) gives an impression of finality. This is alluded to in an inscription on the f. 8r.
</p>
                        <p>Identical in structure, though slightly different in at least the wording of the first chapter, is the equally anonymous Tuhfat al-muluk = Tuhfat al-vuzarā’ described by Munzavī in FNKhF II/2, pp. 1062-3. The earliest of the 31 copies listed is dated 925/1519.
</p>
                        <p>Colophon, f. 8v. Dated 1279/1862-3. Copied by ‘Alīnaqī (probably ‘Alīnaqī ibn Muḥammad Taqī) for Āqā Mīrzā ‘Alī, Mustawfī-i Dīvān-i A‘là. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
